    <div class="container py-3">
  <div class="title h1 text-center">Recent Events</div>
  <!-- Card Start -->
  <div class="card">
    <div class="row ">

      <div class="col-md-7 px-3">
        <div class="card-block px-6">
          <h4 class="card-title">Whine and Cry Night </h4>
          <p class="card-text">
            The Zoom event you have all been waiting for... WHINE AND CRY NIGHT is here ladies and gents. 
                    Get your favorite bottle of wine and log onto Zoom for some quality, ASA bonding time.

                    This event will have set rules, and some prizes. Participants will nominate the 
                    "best whiners", who then would compete in the ultimate whining championship.

                    Here are the ground rules: </p>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                            Interrupting a whiner while they are whining carries a penalty of one sip of the drink.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Interrupting more than 3 times carries a penalty of one full drink
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Each whiner has 2-4 minutes for their initial whine, after which he/she must stop, otherwise every extra 30 second carries a penalty of one sip of the drink.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Exceeding the allowed time by more than two minute carries a penalty of one full drink.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            In the ultimate whining round, each nominee will have up to 6 minutes to whine
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            In the ultimate whining, round nominees cannot whine about previously whined subjects
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            At the end of the initial whining round, nominees would be chosen out of groups based on voting. We will define how groups are divided based on the number of participants.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            At the end of the ultimate whining round, nominees would be given their prizes based on the votes of ALL participants, not including themselves
                        </li>
                    </ul>
